Computerized X-ray Modification CONCEPT

For patrol vehicles with preexisting computer stations. The overall aspect of being able to pick at random objects such as knapsacks bags tarps garbage cans boxes containers of all types and luggage any thing that could be used to conceal suspicious objects contraband weapons evidence objects used or to be used in the committing of an offence
The purpose of the computerized visuals of the observed criteria is to X-ray and identify the contents or what was being concealed.
Aim
To safely detect and defend against growing enthusiasm in  such recent occupancies as pressure cooker explosives concealed weapons such as handguns and concealed weapons such as knives. Also a search for missing items or persons or animals as well as safety precaution when stopping a vehicle or person.
Portable for on foot with cameras.film object and push button automatic conversion to X-ray
